ect on lessons learned working on the program in diverse educational contexts. An important guide for program leaders who wish to develop and sustain an online professional doctorate, An Online Doctorate for Researching Professionals will also be a valuable resource for higher education professionals seeking to include e-learning components in existing on-campus doctoral programs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDistance educationxCurricula. 0aDistance educationxEvaluation. 0aResearchxStudy and teaching (Graduate). 7aEDUCATION / Distance, Open & Online Education.2bisacsh  aresearch, doctorate, adult education, doctoral programs, distance, digital education, blended learning.1 aDawson, Kara, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771992084423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771992084/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles